 325// --- lib_ams.FDb.fdin.Alloc

 336// --- lib_ams.FDb.fdin.AllocMaybe
 337// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 338lib_ams::FFdin* lib_ams::fdin_AllocMaybe() {
 339    lib_ams::FFdin *row = (lib_ams::FFdin*)fdin_AllocMem();

 342    }

 346// --- lib_ams.FDb.fdin.AllocMem
 347// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 348void* lib_ams::fdin_AllocMem() {
 349    u64 new_nelems     = _db.fdin_n+1;
 350    // compute level and index on level
 351    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 352    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 353    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 354    void *ret = NULL;
 355    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 356    lib_ams::FFdin*  lev   = NULL;
 357    if (bsr < 32) {
 358        lev = _db.fdin_lary[bsr];
 359        if (!lev) {
 360            lev=(lib_ams::FFdin*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(lib_ams::FFdin) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 361            _db.fdin_lary[bsr] = lev;
 362        }
 363    }
 364    // allocate element from this level
 365    if (lev) {
 366        _db.fdin_n = i32(new_nelems);
 367        ret = lev + index;
 368    }
 369    return ret;
 370}

 372// --- lib_ams.FDb.fdin.RemoveAll
 373// Remove all elements from Lary
 374void lib_ams::fdin_RemoveAll() {
 375    for (u64 n = _db.fdin_n; n>0; ) {
 376        n--;
 377        fdin_qFind(u64(n)).~FFdin(); // destroy last element
 378        _db.fdin_n = i32(n);
 379    }
 380}

 382// --- lib_ams.FDb.fdin.RemoveLast
 383// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 384void lib_ams::fdin_RemoveLast() {
 385    u64 n = _db.fdin_n;
 386    if (n > 0) {
 387        n -= 1;
 388        fdin_qFind(u64(n)).~FFdin();
 389        _db.fdin_n = i32(n);
 390    }
 391}

 402// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_fdin_eof.Insert
 403// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
 404void lib_ams::cd_fdin_eof_Insert(lib_ams::FFdin& row) {
 405    if (!cd_fdin_eof_InLlistQ(row)) {
 406        if (_db.cd_fdin_eof_head) {
 407            row.cd_fdin_eof_next = _db.cd_fdin_eof_head;
 408            row.cd_fdin_eof_prev = _db.cd_fdin_eof_head->cd_fdin_eof_prev;
 409            row.cd_fdin_eof_prev->cd_fdin_eof_next = &row;
 410            row.cd_fdin_eof_next->cd_fdin_eof_prev = &row;
 411        } else {
 412            row.cd_fdin_eof_next = &row;
 413            row.cd_fdin_eof_prev = &row;
 414            _db.cd_fdin_eof_head = &row;
 415        }
 416        _db.cd_fdin_eof_n++;
 417        if (_db.cd_fdin_eof_head == &row) {
 418            cd_fdin_eof_FirstChanged();
 419        }
 420    }
 421}

 423// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_fdin_eof.Remove
 424// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
 425void lib_ams::cd_fdin_eof_Remove(lib_ams::FFdin& row) {
 426    if (cd_fdin_eof_InLlistQ(row)) {
 427        lib_ams::FFdin* old_head       = _db.cd_fdin_eof_head;
 428        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
 429        lib_ams::FFdin *oldnext = row.cd_fdin_eof_next;
 430        lib_ams::FFdin *oldprev = row.cd_fdin_eof_prev;
 431        oldnext->cd_fdin_eof_prev = oldprev; // remove element from list
 432        oldprev->cd_fdin_eof_next = oldnext;
 433        _db.cd_fdin_eof_n--;  // adjust count
 434        if (&row == _db.cd_fdin_eof_head) {
 435            _db.cd_fdin_eof_head = oldnext==&row ? NULL : oldnext; // adjust list head
 436        }
 437        row.cd_fdin_eof_next = (lib_ams::FFdin*)-1; // mark element as not-in-list);
 438        row.cd_fdin_eof_prev = NULL; // clear back-pointer
 439        if (old_head != _db.cd_fdin_eof_head) {
 440            cd_fdin_eof_FirstChanged();
 441        }
 442    }
 443}

 445// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_fdin_eof.RemoveAll
 446// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
 447void lib_ams::cd_fdin_eof_RemoveAll() {
 448    lib_ams::FFdin* row = _db.cd_fdin_eof_head;
 449    lib_ams::FFdin* head = _db.cd_fdin_eof_head;
 450    _db.cd_fdin_eof_head = NULL;
 451    _db.cd_fdin_eof_n = 0;
 452    bool do_fire = (NULL != row);
 453    while (row) {
 454        lib_ams::FFdin* row_next = row->cd_fdin_eof_next;
 455        row->cd_fdin_eof_next  = (lib_ams::FFdin*)-1;
 456        row->cd_fdin_eof_prev  = NULL;
 457        row = row_next != head  ? row_next : NULL;
 458    }
 459    if (do_fire) {
 460        cd_fdin_eof_FirstChanged();
 461    }
 462}

 464// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_fdin_eof.RemoveFirst
 465// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
 466// Call FirstChanged trigger.
 467lib_ams::FFdin* lib_ams::cd_fdin_eof_RemoveFirst() {
 468    lib_ams::FFdin *row = NULL;
 469    row = _db.cd_fdin_eof_head;
 470    if (row) {
 471        bool hasmore = row!=row->cd_fdin_eof_next;
 472        _db.cd_fdin_eof_head = hasmore ? row->cd_fdin_eof_next : NULL;
 473        row->cd_fdin_eof_next->cd_fdin_eof_prev = row->cd_fdin_eof_prev;
 474        row->cd_fdin_eof_prev->cd_fdin_eof_next = row->cd_fdin_eof_next;
 475        row->cd_fdin_eof_prev = NULL;
 476        _db.cd_fdin_eof_n--;
 477        row->cd_fdin_eof_next = (lib_ams::FFdin*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
 478        cd_fdin_eof_FirstChanged();
 479    }
 480    return row;
 481}

 516// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_fdin_read.Insert
 517// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
 518void lib_ams::cd_fdin_read_Insert(lib_ams::FFdin& row) {
 519    if (!cd_fdin_read_InLlistQ(row)) {
 520        if (_db.cd_fdin_read_head) {
 521            row.cd_fdin_read_next = _db.cd_fdin_read_head;
 522            row.cd_fdin_read_prev = _db.cd_fdin_read_head->cd_fdin_read_prev;
 523            row.cd_fdin_read_prev->cd_fdin_read_next = &row;
 524            row.cd_fdin_read_next->cd_fdin_read_prev = &row;
 525        } else {
 526            row.cd_fdin_read_next = &row;
 527            row.cd_fdin_read_prev = &row;
 528            _db.cd_fdin_read_head = &row;
 529        }
 530        _db.cd_fdin_read_n++;
 531        if (_db.cd_fdin_read_head == &row) {
 532            cd_fdin_read_FirstChanged();
 533        }
 534    }
 535}
 536
 537// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_fdin_read.Remove
 538// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
 539void lib_ams::cd_fdin_read_Remove(lib_ams::FFdin& row) {
 540    if (cd_fdin_read_InLlistQ(row)) {
 541        lib_ams::FFdin* old_head       = _db.cd_fdin_read_head;
 542        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
 543        lib_ams::FFdin *oldnext = row.cd_fdin_read_next;
 544        lib_ams::FFdin *oldprev = row.cd_fdin_read_prev;
 545        oldnext->cd_fdin_read_prev = oldprev; // remove element from list
 546        oldprev->cd_fdin_read_next = oldnext;
 547        _db.cd_fdin_read_n--;  // adjust count
 548        if (&row == _db.cd_fdin_read_head) {
 549            _db.cd_fdin_read_head = oldnext==&row ? NULL : oldnext; // adjust list head
 550        }
 551        row.cd_fdin_read_next = (lib_ams::FFdin*)-1; // mark element as not-in-list);
 552        row.cd_fdin_read_prev = NULL; // clear back-pointer
 553        if (old_head != _db.cd_fdin_read_head) {
 554            cd_fdin_read_FirstChanged();
 555        }
 556    }
 557}

 630// --- lib_ams.FDb._db.Step
 631// Main step
 632void lib_ams::Step() {
 633    cd_fdin_eof_Call();
 634    cd_fdin_read_Call();
 635    cd_stream_hb_Call();
 636    zd_flush_Call();
 637    cd_poll_read_Call();
 638}

 670// --- lib_ams.FDb._db.LoadTuplesMaybe
 671// Load all finputs from given directory.
 672bool lib_ams::LoadTuplesMaybe(algo::strptr root, bool recursive) {
 673    bool retval = true;
 674    if (FileQ(root)) {
 675        retval = lib_ams::LoadTuplesFile(root, recursive);
 676    } else if (root == "-") {
 677        retval = lib_ams::LoadTuplesFd(algo::Fildes(0),"(stdin)",recursive);
 678    } else if (DirectoryQ(root)) {
 679        retval = retval && lib_ams::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.dispsigcheck"),recursive);
 680    } else {
 681        algo_lib::SaveBadTag("path", root);
 682        algo_lib::SaveBadTag("comment", "Wrong working directory?");
 683        retval = false;
 684    }
 685    return retval;
 686}

 688// --- lib_ams.FDb._db.LoadTuplesFile
 689// Load all finputs from given file.
 690// Read tuples from file FNAME into this namespace's in-memory database.
 691// If RECURSIVE is TRUE, then also load these tuples into any parent namespaces
 692// It a file referred to by FNAME is missing, no error is reported (it's considered an empty set).
 693// Function returns TRUE if all records were parsed and inserted without error.
 694// If the function returns FALSE, use algo_lib::DetachBadTags() for error description
 695bool lib_ams::LoadTuplesFile(algo::strptr fname, bool recursive) {
 696    bool retval = true;
 697    algo_lib::FFildes fildes;
 698    // missing files are not an error
 699    fildes.fd = OpenRead(fname,algo::FileFlags());
 700    if (ValidQ(fildes.fd)) {
 701        retval = LoadTuplesFd(fildes.fd, fname, recursive);
 702    }
 703    return retval;
 704}
 705
 706// --- lib_ams.FDb._db.LoadTuplesFd
 707// Load all finputs from given file descriptor.
 708bool lib_ams::LoadTuplesFd(algo::Fildes fd, algo::strptr fname, bool recursive) {
 709    bool retval = true;
 710    ind_beg(algo::FileLine_curs,line,fd) {
 711        if (recursive) {
 712            retval = retval && algo_lib::InsertStrptrMaybe(line);
 713        }
 714        if (!retval) {
 715            algo_lib::_db.errtext << eol
 716            << fname << ":"
 717            << (ind_curs(line).i+1)
 718            << ": " << line << eol;
 719            break;
 720        }
 721    }ind_end;
 722    return retval;
 723}

 726// Load specified ssimfile.
 727bool lib_ams::LoadSsimfileMaybe(algo::strptr fname, bool recursive) {
 728    bool retval = true;
 729    if (FileQ(fname)) {
 730        retval = lib_ams::LoadTuplesFile(fname, recursive);
 731    }
 732    return retval;
 733}

 763// --- lib_ams.FDb.zd_flush.Insert
 764// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
 765void lib_ams::zd_flush_Insert(lib_ams::FWritefile& row) {
 766    if (!zd_flush_InLlistQ(row)) {
 767        lib_ams::FWritefile* old_tail = _db.zd_flush_tail;
 768        row.zd_flush_next = NULL;
 769        row.zd_flush_prev = old_tail;
 770        _db.zd_flush_tail = &row;
 771        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_row_a = &old_tail->zd_flush_next;
 772        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_row_b = &_db.zd_flush_head;
 773        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
 774        *new_row = &row;
 775        _db.zd_flush_n++;
 776        if (_db.zd_flush_head == &row) {
 777            zd_flush_FirstChanged();
 778        }
 779    }
 780}
 781
 782// --- lib_ams.FDb.zd_flush.Remove
 783// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
 784void lib_ams::zd_flush_Remove(lib_ams::FWritefile& row) {
 785    if (zd_flush_InLlistQ(row)) {
 786        lib_ams::FWritefile* old_head       = _db.zd_flush_head;
 787        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
 788        lib_ams::FWritefile* prev = row.zd_flush_prev;
 789        lib_ams::FWritefile* next = row.zd_flush_next;
 790        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
 791        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_next_a = &prev->zd_flush_next;
 792        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_next_b = &_db.zd_flush_head;
 793        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
 794        *new_next = next;
 795        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
 796        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_prev_a = &next->zd_flush_prev;
 797        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_prev_b = &_db.zd_flush_tail;
 798        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_prev = next ? new_prev_a : new_prev_b;
 799        *new_prev = prev;
 800        _db.zd_flush_n--;
 801        row.zd_flush_next=(lib_ams::FWritefile*)-1; // not-in-list
 802        if (old_head != _db.zd_flush_head) {
 803            zd_flush_FirstChanged();
 804        }
 805    }
 806}

 808// --- lib_ams.FDb.zd_flush.RemoveAll
 809// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
 810void lib_ams::zd_flush_RemoveAll() {
 811    lib_ams::FWritefile* row = _db.zd_flush_head;
 812    _db.zd_flush_head = NULL;
 813    _db.zd_flush_tail = NULL;
 814    _db.zd_flush_n = 0;
 815    bool do_fire = (NULL != row);
 816    while (row) {
 817        lib_ams::FWritefile* row_next = row->zd_flush_next;
 818        row->zd_flush_next  = (lib_ams::FWritefile*)-1;
 819        row->zd_flush_prev  = NULL;
 820        row = row_next;
 821    }
 822    if (do_fire) {
 823        zd_flush_FirstChanged();
 824    }
 825}

 827// --- lib_ams.FDb.zd_flush.RemoveFirst
 828// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
 829// Call FirstChanged trigger.
 830lib_ams::FWritefile* lib_ams::zd_flush_RemoveFirst() {
 831    lib_ams::FWritefile *row = NULL;
 832    row = _db.zd_flush_head;
 833    if (row) {
 834        lib_ams::FWritefile *next = row->zd_flush_next;
 835        _db.zd_flush_head = next;
 836        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_end_a = &next->zd_flush_prev;
 837        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_end_b = &_db.zd_flush_tail;
 838        lib_ams::FWritefile **new_end = next ? new_end_a : new_end_b;
 839        *new_end = NULL;
 840        _db.zd_flush_n--;
 841        row->zd_flush_next = (lib_ams::FWritefile*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
 842        zd_flush_FirstChanged();
 843    }
 844    return row;
 845}

 852// --- lib_ams.FDb.zd_flush.UpdateCycles
 853// Update cycles count from previous clock capture
 854inline static void lib_ams::zd_flush_UpdateCycles() {

 859// --- lib_ams.FDb.zd_flush.Call
 860inline static void lib_ams::zd_flush_Call() {
 861    if (!lib_ams::zd_flush_EmptyQ()) { // fstep:lib_ams.FDb.zd_flush
 862        if (lib_ams::_db.zd_flush_next < algo_lib::_db.clock) {
 863            u64 effective_delay = lib_ams::_db.zd_flush_delay / u64_Max(1,lib_ams::zd_flush_N());
 864            lib_ams::_db.zd_flush_next = algo_lib::_db.clock + algo::SchedTime(effective_delay);
 865            lib_ams::zd_flush_Step(); // steptype:InlineRecur: call function every N clock cycles
 866            zd_flush_UpdateCycles();
 867        }
 868        algo_lib::_db.next_loop.value = u64_Min(lib_ams::_db.zd_flush_next, algo_lib::_db.next_loop);
 869    }
 870}
 871
 872// --- lib_ams.FDb.zd_flush.SetDelay
 873// Set inter-step delay to specified value.
 874// The difference between new delay and current delay is added to the next scheduled time.
 875void lib_ams::zd_flush_SetDelay(algo::SchedTime delay) {
 876    i64 diff = delay.value - lib_ams::_db.zd_flush_delay.value;
 877    lib_ams::_db.zd_flush_delay = delay;
 878    if (diff > 0) {
 879        lib_ams::_db.zd_flush_next.value += diff;
 880    } else {
 881        lib_ams::_db.zd_flush_next.value = algo::u64_SubClip(lib_ams::_db.zd_flush_next.value,-diff);
 882    }
 883}

 885// --- lib_ams.FDb.stream.Alloc
 886// Allocate memory for new default row.
 887// If out of memory, process is killed.
 888lib_ams::FStream& lib_ams::stream_Alloc() {
 889    lib_ams::FStream* row = stream_AllocMaybe();
 890    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 891        FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.out_of_mem  field:lib_ams.FDb.stream  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 892    }
 893    return *row;
 894}

 896// --- lib_ams.FDb.stream.AllocMaybe
 897// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 898lib_ams::FStream* lib_ams::stream_AllocMaybe() {
 899    lib_ams::FStream *row = (lib_ams::FStream*)stream_AllocMem();
 900    if (row) {
 901        new (row) lib_ams::FStream; // call constructor
 902    }
 903    return row;
 904}
 905
 906// --- lib_ams.FDb.stream.AllocMem
 907// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 908void* lib_ams::stream_AllocMem() {
 909    u64 new_nelems     = _db.stream_n+1;
 910    // compute level and index on level
 911    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 912    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 913    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 914    void *ret = NULL;
 915    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 916    lib_ams::FStream*  lev   = NULL;
 917    if (bsr < 32) {
 918        lev = _db.stream_lary[bsr];
 919        if (!lev) {
 920            lev=(lib_ams::FStream*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(lib_ams::FStream) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 921            _db.stream_lary[bsr] = lev;
 922        }
 923    }
 924    // allocate element from this level
 925    if (lev) {
 926        _db.stream_n = i32(new_nelems);
 927        ret = lev + index;
 928    }
 929    return ret;
 930}
 931
 932// --- lib_ams.FDb.stream.RemoveAll
 933// Remove all elements from Lary
 934void lib_ams::stream_RemoveAll() {
 935    for (u64 n = _db.stream_n; n>0; ) {
 936        n--;
 937        stream_qFind(u64(n)).~FStream(); // destroy last element
 938        _db.stream_n = i32(n);
 939    }
 940}
 941
 942// --- lib_ams.FDb.stream.RemoveLast
 943// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 944void lib_ams::stream_RemoveLast() {
 945    u64 n = _db.stream_n;
 946    if (n > 0) {
 947        n -= 1;
 948        stream_qFind(u64(n)).~FStream();
 949        _db.stream_n = i32(n);
 950    }
 951}

 953// --- lib_ams.FDb.stream.XrefMaybe
 954// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 955// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 956bool lib_ams::stream_XrefMaybe(lib_ams::FStream &row) {
 957    bool retval = true;
 958    (void)row;
 959    lib_ams::FStreamType* p_stream_type = lib_ams::ind_streamtype_Find(row.stream_id.stream_type);
 960    if (UNLIKELY(!p_stream_type)) {
 961        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "lib_ams.bad_xref  index:lib_ams.FDb.ind_streamtype" << Keyval("key", row.stream_id.stream_type);
 962        return false;
 963    }
 964    // stream: save pointer to stream_type
 965    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 966        row.p_streamtype = p_stream_type;
 967    }
 968    // insert stream into index ind_stream
 969    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 970        bool success = ind_stream_InsertMaybe(row);
 971        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 972            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 973            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "lib_ams.duplicate_key  xref:lib_ams.FDb.ind_stream"; // check for duplicate key
 974            return false;
 975        }
 976    }
 977    return retval;
 978}
 979
 980// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_stream.Find
 981// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 982lib_ams::FStream* lib_ams::ind_stream_Find(ams::StreamId key) {
 983    u32 index = ams::StreamId_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_stream_buckets_n - 1);
 984    lib_ams::FStream* *e = &_db.ind_stream_buckets_elems[index];
 985    lib_ams::FStream* ret=NULL;
 986    do {
 987        ret       = *e;
 988        bool done = !ret || (*ret).stream_id == key;
 989        if (done) break;
 990        e         = &ret->ind_stream_next;
 991    } while (true);
 992    return ret;
 993}

 995// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_stream.FindX
 996// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
 997lib_ams::FStream& lib_ams::ind_stream_FindX(ams::StreamId key) {
 998    lib_ams::FStream* ret = ind_stream_Find(key);
 999    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "lib_ams.key_error  table:ind_stream  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
1000    return *ret;
1001}

1003// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_stream.InsertMaybe
1004// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
1005bool lib_ams::ind_stream_InsertMaybe(lib_ams::FStream& row) {
1006    ind_stream_Reserve(1);
1007    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
1008    if (LIKELY(row.ind_stream_next == (lib_ams::FStream*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1009        u32 index = ams::StreamId_Hash(0, row.stream_id) & (_db.ind_stream_buckets_n - 1);
1010        lib_ams::FStream* *prev = &_db.ind_stream_buckets_elems[index];
1011        do {
1012            lib_ams::FStream* ret = *prev;
1013            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
1014                break;
1015            }
1016            if ((*ret).stream_id == row.stream_id) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
1017                retval = false;
1018                break;
1019            }
1020            prev = &ret->ind_stream_next;
1021        } while (true);
1022        if (retval) {
1023            row.ind_stream_next = *prev;
1024            _db.ind_stream_n++;
1025            *prev = &row;
1026        }
1027    }
1028    return retval;
1029}
1030
1031// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_stream.Remove
1032// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
1033void lib_ams::ind_stream_Remove(lib_ams::FStream& row) {
1034    if (LIKELY(row.ind_stream_next != (lib_ams::FStream*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1035        u32 index = ams::StreamId_Hash(0, row.stream_id) & (_db.ind_stream_buckets_n - 1);
1036        lib_ams::FStream* *prev = &_db.ind_stream_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
1037        while (lib_ams::FStream *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
1038            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
1039                *prev = next->ind_stream_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
1040                _db.ind_stream_n--;
1041                row.ind_stream_next = (lib_ams::FStream*)-1;// not-in-hash
1042                break;
1043            }
1044            prev = &next->ind_stream_next;
1045        }
1046    }
1047}
1048
1049// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_stream.Reserve
1050// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
1051void lib_ams::ind_stream_Reserve(int n) {
1052    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_stream_buckets_n;
1053    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_stream_n + n;
1054    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
1055    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
1056        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
1057        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(lib_ams::FStream*);
1058        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(lib_ams::FStream*);
1059        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
1060        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
1061        lib_ams::FStream* *new_buckets = (lib_ams::FStream**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
1062        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
1063            FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.out_of_memory  field:lib_ams.FDb.ind_stream");
1064        }
1065        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
1066        // rehash all entries
1067        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_stream_buckets_n; i++) {
1068            lib_ams::FStream* elem = _db.ind_stream_buckets_elems[i];
1069            while (elem) {
1070                lib_ams::FStream &row        = *elem;
1071                lib_ams::FStream* next       = row.ind_stream_next;
1072                u32 index          = ams::StreamId_Hash(0, row.stream_id) & (new_nbuckets-1);
1073                row.ind_stream_next     = new_buckets[index];
1074                new_buckets[index] = &row;
1075                elem               = next;
1076            }
1077        }
1078        // free old array
1079        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_stream_buckets_elems, old_size);
1080        _db.ind_stream_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
1081        _db.ind_stream_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
1082    }
1083}

1085// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_stream_hb.Insert
1086// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
1087void lib_ams::cd_stream_hb_Insert(lib_ams::FStream& row) {
1088    if (!cd_stream_hb_InLlistQ(row)) {
1089        if (_db.cd_stream_hb_head) {
1090            row.cd_stream_hb_next = _db.cd_stream_hb_head;
1091            row.cd_stream_hb_prev = _db.cd_stream_hb_head->cd_stream_hb_prev;
1092            row.cd_stream_hb_prev->cd_stream_hb_next = &row;
1093            row.cd_stream_hb_next->cd_stream_hb_prev = &row;
1094        } else {
1095            row.cd_stream_hb_next = &row;
1096            row.cd_stream_hb_prev = &row;
1097            _db.cd_stream_hb_head = &row;
1098        }
1099        _db.cd_stream_hb_n++;
1100        if (_db.cd_stream_hb_head == &row) {
1101            cd_stream_hb_FirstChanged();
1102        }
1103    }
1104}
1105
1106// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_stream_hb.Remove
1107// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
1108void lib_ams::cd_stream_hb_Remove(lib_ams::FStream& row) {
1109    if (cd_stream_hb_InLlistQ(row)) {
1110        lib_ams::FStream* old_head       = _db.cd_stream_hb_head;
1111        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
1112        lib_ams::FStream *oldnext = row.cd_stream_hb_next;
1113        lib_ams::FStream *oldprev = row.cd_stream_hb_prev;
1114        oldnext->cd_stream_hb_prev = oldprev; // remove element from list
1115        oldprev->cd_stream_hb_next = oldnext;
1116        _db.cd_stream_hb_n--;  // adjust count
1117        if (&row == _db.cd_stream_hb_head) {
1118            _db.cd_stream_hb_head = oldnext==&row ? NULL : oldnext; // adjust list head
1119        }
1120        row.cd_stream_hb_next = (lib_ams::FStream*)-1; // mark element as not-in-list);
1121        row.cd_stream_hb_prev = NULL; // clear back-pointer
1122        if (old_head != _db.cd_stream_hb_head) {
1123            cd_stream_hb_FirstChanged();
1124        }
1125    }
1126}
1127
1128// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_stream_hb.RemoveAll
1129// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
1130void lib_ams::cd_stream_hb_RemoveAll() {
1131    lib_ams::FStream* row = _db.cd_stream_hb_head;
1132    lib_ams::FStream* head = _db.cd_stream_hb_head;
1133    _db.cd_stream_hb_head = NULL;
1134    _db.cd_stream_hb_n = 0;
1135    bool do_fire = (NULL != row);
1136    while (row) {
1137        lib_ams::FStream* row_next = row->cd_stream_hb_next;
1138        row->cd_stream_hb_next  = (lib_ams::FStream*)-1;
1139        row->cd_stream_hb_prev  = NULL;
1140        row = row_next != head  ? row_next : NULL;
1141    }
1142    if (do_fire) {
1143        cd_stream_hb_FirstChanged();
1144    }
1145}

1147// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_stream_hb.RemoveFirst
1148// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
1149// Call FirstChanged trigger.
1150lib_ams::FStream* lib_ams::cd_stream_hb_RemoveFirst() {
1151    lib_ams::FStream *row = NULL;
1152    row = _db.cd_stream_hb_head;
1153    if (row) {
1154        bool hasmore = row!=row->cd_stream_hb_next;
1155        _db.cd_stream_hb_head = hasmore ? row->cd_stream_hb_next : NULL;
1156        row->cd_stream_hb_next->cd_stream_hb_prev = row->cd_stream_hb_prev;
1157        row->cd_stream_hb_prev->cd_stream_hb_next = row->cd_stream_hb_next;
1158        row->cd_stream_hb_prev = NULL;
1159        _db.cd_stream_hb_n--;
1160        row->cd_stream_hb_next = (lib_ams::FStream*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
1161        cd_stream_hb_FirstChanged();
1162    }
1163    return row;
1164}

1190// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_stream_hb.Call
1191inline static void lib_ams::cd_stream_hb_Call() {
1192    if (!lib_ams::cd_stream_hb_EmptyQ()) { // fstep:lib_ams.FDb.cd_stream_hb
1193        if (lib_ams::_db.cd_stream_hb_next < algo_lib::_db.clock) {
1194            u64 effective_delay = lib_ams::_db.cd_stream_hb_delay / u64_Max(1,lib_ams::cd_stream_hb_N());
1195            lib_ams::_db.cd_stream_hb_next = algo_lib::_db.clock + algo::SchedTime(effective_delay);
1196            lib_ams::cd_stream_hb_Step(); // steptype:InlineRecur: call function every N clock cycles
1197            cd_stream_hb_UpdateCycles();
1198        }
1199        algo_lib::_db.next_loop.value = u64_Min(lib_ams::_db.cd_stream_hb_next, algo_lib::_db.next_loop);
1200    }
1201}

1203// --- lib_ams.FDb.cd_stream_hb.SetDelay
1204// Set inter-step delay to specified value.
1205// The difference between new delay and current delay is added to the next scheduled time.
1206void lib_ams::cd_stream_hb_SetDelay(algo::SchedTime delay) {
1207    i64 diff = delay.value - lib_ams::_db.cd_stream_hb_delay.value;
1208    lib_ams::_db.cd_stream_hb_delay = delay;
1209    if (diff > 0) {
1210        lib_ams::_db.cd_stream_hb_next.value += diff;
1211    } else {
1212        lib_ams::_db.cd_stream_hb_next.value = algo::u64_SubClip(lib_ams::_db.cd_stream_hb_next.value,-diff);
1213    }
1214}

1358// --- lib_ams.FDb.proc.AllocMem
1359// Allocate space for one element
1360// If no memory available, return NULL.
1361void* lib_ams::proc_AllocMem() {
1362    lib_ams::FProc *row = _db.proc_free;
1363    if (UNLIKELY(!row)) {
1364        proc_Reserve(1);
1365        row = _db.proc_free;
1366    }
1367    if (row) {
1368        _db.proc_free = row->proc_next;
1369    }
1370    return row;
1371}

1373// --- lib_ams.FDb.proc.FreeMem
1374// Remove mem from all global and cross indices, then deallocate mem
1375void lib_ams::proc_FreeMem(lib_ams::FProc &row) {
1376    if (UNLIKELY(row.proc_next != (lib_ams::FProc*)-1)) {
1377        FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.tpool_double_delete  pool:lib_ams.FDb.proc  comment:'double deletion caught'");
1378    }
1379    row.proc_next = _db.proc_free; // insert into free list
1380    _db.proc_free  = &row;
1381}

1383// --- lib_ams.FDb.proc.Reserve
1384// Preallocate memory for N more elements
1385// Return number of elements actually reserved.
1386u64 lib_ams::proc_Reserve(u64 n_elems) {
1387    u64 ret = 0;
1388    while (ret < n_elems) {
1389        u64 size = _db.proc_blocksize; // underlying allocator is probably Lpool
1390        u64 reserved = proc_ReserveMem(size);
1391        ret += reserved;
1392        if (reserved == 0) {
1393            break;
1394        }
1395    }
1396    return ret;
1397}
1398
1399// --- lib_ams.FDb.proc.ReserveMem
1400// Allocate block of given size, break up into small elements and append to free list.
1401// Return number of elements reserved.
1402u64 lib_ams::proc_ReserveMem(u64 size) {
1403    u64 ret = 0;
1404    if (size >= sizeof(lib_ams::FProc)) {
1405        lib_ams::FProc *mem = (lib_ams::FProc*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(size);
1406        ret = mem ? size / sizeof(lib_ams::FProc) : 0;
1407        // add newly allocated elements to the free list;
1408        for (u64 i=0; i < ret; i++) {
1409            mem[i].proc_next = _db.proc_free;
1410            _db.proc_free = mem+i;
1411        }
1412    }
1413    return ret;
1414}

1416// --- lib_ams.FDb.proc.XrefMaybe
1417// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1418// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1419bool lib_ams::proc_XrefMaybe(lib_ams::FProc &row) {
1420    bool retval = true;
1421    (void)row;
1422    // insert proc into index ind_proc
1423    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1424        bool success = ind_proc_InsertMaybe(row);
1425        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
1426            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
1427            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "lib_ams.duplicate_key  xref:lib_ams.FDb.ind_proc"; // check for duplicate key
1428            return false;
1429        }
1430    }
1431    // insert proc into index zd_proc
1432    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1433        zd_proc_Insert(row);
1434    }
1435    return retval;
1436}

1438// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_proc.Find
1439// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
1440lib_ams::FProc* lib_ams::ind_proc_Find(ams::ProcId key) {
1441    u32 index = ams::ProcId_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_proc_buckets_n - 1);
1442    lib_ams::FProc* *e = &_db.ind_proc_buckets_elems[index];
1443    lib_ams::FProc* ret=NULL;
1444    do {
1445        ret       = *e;
1446        bool done = !ret || (*ret).proc_id == key;
1447        if (done) break;
1448        e         = &ret->ind_proc_next;
1449    } while (true);
1450    return ret;
1451}

1453// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_proc.FindX
1454// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
1455lib_ams::FProc& lib_ams::ind_proc_FindX(ams::ProcId key) {
1456    lib_ams::FProc* ret = ind_proc_Find(key);
1457    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "lib_ams.key_error  table:ind_proc  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
1458    return *ret;
1459}

1461// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_proc.GetOrCreate
1462// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
1463lib_ams::FProc& lib_ams::ind_proc_GetOrCreate(ams::ProcId key) {
1464    lib_ams::FProc* ret = ind_proc_Find(key);
1465    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
1466        ret         = &proc_Alloc();
1467        (*ret).proc_id = key;
1468        bool good = proc_XrefMaybe(*ret);
1469        if (!good) {
1470            proc_Delete(*ret); // delete offending row, any existin xrefs are cleared
1471            ret = NULL;
1472        }
1473    }
1474    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "lib_ams.create_error  table:ind_proc  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
1475    return *ret;
1476}
1477
1478// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_proc.InsertMaybe
1479// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
1480bool lib_ams::ind_proc_InsertMaybe(lib_ams::FProc& row) {
1481    ind_proc_Reserve(1);
1482    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
1483    if (LIKELY(row.ind_proc_next == (lib_ams::FProc*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1484        u32 index = ams::ProcId_Hash(0, row.proc_id) & (_db.ind_proc_buckets_n - 1);
1485        lib_ams::FProc* *prev = &_db.ind_proc_buckets_elems[index];
1486        do {
1487            lib_ams::FProc* ret = *prev;
1488            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
1489                break;
1490            }
1491            if ((*ret).proc_id == row.proc_id) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
1492                retval = false;
1493                break;
1494            }
1495            prev = &ret->ind_proc_next;
1496        } while (true);
1497        if (retval) {
1498            row.ind_proc_next = *prev;
1499            _db.ind_proc_n++;
1500            *prev = &row;
1501        }
1502    }
1503    return retval;
1504}
1505
1506// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_proc.Remove
1507// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
1508void lib_ams::ind_proc_Remove(lib_ams::FProc& row) {
1509    if (LIKELY(row.ind_proc_next != (lib_ams::FProc*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1510        u32 index = ams::ProcId_Hash(0, row.proc_id) & (_db.ind_proc_buckets_n - 1);
1511        lib_ams::FProc* *prev = &_db.ind_proc_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
1512        while (lib_ams::FProc *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
1513            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
1514                *prev = next->ind_proc_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
1515                _db.ind_proc_n--;
1516                row.ind_proc_next = (lib_ams::FProc*)-1;// not-in-hash
1517                break;
1518            }
1519            prev = &next->ind_proc_next;
1520        }
1521    }
1522}
1523
1524// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_proc.Reserve
1525// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
1526void lib_ams::ind_proc_Reserve(int n) {
1527    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_proc_buckets_n;
1528    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_proc_n + n;
1529    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
1530    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
1531        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
1532        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(lib_ams::FProc*);
1533        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(lib_ams::FProc*);
1534        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
1535        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
1536        lib_ams::FProc* *new_buckets = (lib_ams::FProc**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
1537        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
1538            FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.out_of_memory  field:lib_ams.FDb.ind_proc");
1539        }
1540        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
1541        // rehash all entries
1542        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_proc_buckets_n; i++) {
1543            lib_ams::FProc* elem = _db.ind_proc_buckets_elems[i];
1544            while (elem) {
1545                lib_ams::FProc &row        = *elem;
1546                lib_ams::FProc* next       = row.ind_proc_next;
1547                u32 index          = ams::ProcId_Hash(0, row.proc_id) & (new_nbuckets-1);
1548                row.ind_proc_next     = new_buckets[index];
1549                new_buckets[index] = &row;
1550                elem               = next;
1551            }
1552        }
1553        // free old array
1554        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_proc_buckets_elems, old_size);
1555        _db.ind_proc_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
1556        _db.ind_proc_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
1557    }
1558}

1588// --- lib_ams.FDb.member.AllocMem
1589// Allocate space for one element
1590// If no memory available, return NULL.
1591void* lib_ams::member_AllocMem() {
1592    lib_ams::FMember *row = _db.member_free;
1593    if (UNLIKELY(!row)) {
1594        member_Reserve(1);
1595        row = _db.member_free;
1596    }
1597    if (row) {
1598        _db.member_free = row->member_next;
1599    }
1600    return row;
1601}
1602
1603// --- lib_ams.FDb.member.FreeMem
1604// Remove mem from all global and cross indices, then deallocate mem
1605void lib_ams::member_FreeMem(lib_ams::FMember &row) {
1606    if (UNLIKELY(row.member_next != (lib_ams::FMember*)-1)) {
1607        FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.tpool_double_delete  pool:lib_ams.FDb.member  comment:'double deletion caught'");
1608    }
1609    row.member_next = _db.member_free; // insert into free list
1610    _db.member_free  = &row;
1611}
1612
1613// --- lib_ams.FDb.member.Reserve
1614// Preallocate memory for N more elements
1615// Return number of elements actually reserved.
1616u64 lib_ams::member_Reserve(u64 n_elems) {
1617    u64 ret = 0;
1618    while (ret < n_elems) {
1619        u64 size = _db.member_blocksize; // underlying allocator is probably Lpool
1620        u64 reserved = member_ReserveMem(size);
1621        ret += reserved;
1622        if (reserved == 0) {
1623            break;
1624        }
1625    }
1626    return ret;
1627}
1628
1629// --- lib_ams.FDb.member.ReserveMem
1630// Allocate block of given size, break up into small elements and append to free list.
1631// Return number of elements reserved.
1632u64 lib_ams::member_ReserveMem(u64 size) {
1633    u64 ret = 0;
1634    if (size >= sizeof(lib_ams::FMember)) {
1635        lib_ams::FMember *mem = (lib_ams::FMember*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(size);
1636        ret = mem ? size / sizeof(lib_ams::FMember) : 0;
1637        // add newly allocated elements to the free list;
1638        for (u64 i=0; i < ret; i++) {
1639            mem[i].member_next = _db.member_free;
1640            _db.member_free = mem+i;
1641        }
1642    }
1643    return ret;
1644}

1646// --- lib_ams.FDb.member.XrefMaybe
1647// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1648// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1649bool lib_ams::member_XrefMaybe(lib_ams::FMember &row) {
1650    bool retval = true;
1651    (void)row;
1652    lib_ams::FStream* p_stream_id = lib_ams::ind_stream_Find(row.member.stream_id);
1653    if (UNLIKELY(!p_stream_id)) {
1654        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "lib_ams.bad_xref  index:lib_ams.FDb.ind_stream" << Keyval("key", row.member.stream_id);
1655        return false;
1656    }
1657    // member: save pointer to stream_id
1658    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1659        row.p_stream = p_stream_id;
1660    }
1661    lib_ams::FProc* p_proc_id = lib_ams::ind_proc_Find(row.member.proc_id);
1662    if (UNLIKELY(!p_proc_id)) {
1663        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "lib_ams.bad_xref  index:lib_ams.FDb.ind_proc" << Keyval("key", row.member.proc_id);
1664        return false;
1665    }
1666    // member: save pointer to proc_id
1667    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1668        row.p_proc = p_proc_id;
1669    }
1670    // insert member into index ind_member
1671    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1672        bool success = ind_member_InsertMaybe(row);
1673        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
1674            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
1675            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "lib_ams.duplicate_key  xref:lib_ams.FDb.ind_member"; // check for duplicate key
1676            return false;
1677        }
1678    }
1679    // insert member into index zd_member_bystream
1680    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1681        zd_member_bystream_Insert(*p_stream_id, row);
1682    }
1683    // insert member into index zd_member_byproc
1684    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1685        zd_member_byproc_Insert(*p_proc_id, row);
1686    }
1687    return retval;
1688}

1759// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_member.Reserve
1760// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
1761void lib_ams::ind_member_Reserve(int n) {
1762    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_member_buckets_n;
1763    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_member_n + n;
1764    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
1765    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
1766        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
1767        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(lib_ams::FMember*);
1768        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(lib_ams::FMember*);
1769        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
1770        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
1771        lib_ams::FMember* *new_buckets = (lib_ams::FMember**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
1772        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {

1774        }
1775        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
1776        // rehash all entries
1777        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_member_buckets_n; i++) {
1778            lib_ams::FMember* elem = _db.ind_member_buckets_elems[i];
1779            while (elem) {

1781                lib_ams::FMember* next       = row.ind_member_next;

1783                row.ind_member_next     = new_buckets[index];
1784                new_buckets[index] = &row;
1785                elem               = next;
1786            }
1787        }
1788        // free old array
1789        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_member_buckets_elems, old_size);
1790        _db.ind_member_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
1791        _db.ind_member_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
1792    }
1793}

1816// --- lib_ams.FDb.streamtype.InsertMaybe
1817// Create new row from struct.
1818// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
1819lib_ams::FStreamType* lib_ams::streamtype_InsertMaybe(const amsdb::StreamType &value) {
1820    lib_ams::FStreamType *row = &streamtype_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
1821    streamtype_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<amsdb::StreamType&>(value));
1822    bool ok = streamtype_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
1823    if (!ok) {
1824        streamtype_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
1825        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
1826    }
1827    return row;
1828}
1829
1830// --- lib_ams.FDb.streamtype.AllocMem
1831// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
1832void* lib_ams::streamtype_AllocMem() {
1833    u64 new_nelems     = _db.streamtype_n+1;
1834    // compute level and index on level
1835    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
1836    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
1837    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
1838    void *ret = NULL;
1839    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
1840    lib_ams::FStreamType*  lev   = NULL;
1841    if (bsr < 32) {
1842        lev = _db.streamtype_lary[bsr];
1843        if (!lev) {
1844            lev=(lib_ams::FStreamType*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(lib_ams::FStreamType) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
1845            _db.streamtype_lary[bsr] = lev;
1846        }
1847    }
1848    // allocate element from this level
1849    if (lev) {
1850        _db.streamtype_n = i32(new_nelems);
1851        ret = lev + index;
1852    }
1853    return ret;
1854}
1855
1856// --- lib_ams.FDb.streamtype.RemoveAll
1857// Remove all elements from Lary
1858void lib_ams::streamtype_RemoveAll() {
1859    for (u64 n = _db.streamtype_n; n>0; ) {
1860        n--;
1861        streamtype_qFind(u64(n)).~FStreamType(); // destroy last element
1862        _db.streamtype_n = i32(n);
1863    }
1864}
1865
1866// --- lib_ams.FDb.streamtype.RemoveLast
1867// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
1868void lib_ams::streamtype_RemoveLast() {
1869    u64 n = _db.streamtype_n;
1870    if (n > 0) {
1871        n -= 1;
1872        streamtype_qFind(u64(n)).~FStreamType();
1873        _db.streamtype_n = i32(n);
1874    }
1875}

1939// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_streamtype.GetOrCreate
1940// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
1941lib_ams::FStreamType& lib_ams::ind_streamtype_GetOrCreate(ams::StreamType key) {
1942    lib_ams::FStreamType* ret = ind_streamtype_Find(key);
1943    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
1944        ret         = &streamtype_Alloc();
1945        (*ret).id = key;
1946        bool good = streamtype_XrefMaybe(*ret);
1947        if (!good) {
1948            streamtype_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
1949            ret = NULL;
1950        }
1951    }
1952    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "lib_ams.create_error  table:ind_streamtype  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
1953    return *ret;
1954}
1955
1956// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_streamtype.InsertMaybe
1957// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
1958bool lib_ams::ind_streamtype_InsertMaybe(lib_ams::FStreamType& row) {
1959    ind_streamtype_Reserve(1);
1960    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
1961    if (LIKELY(row.ind_streamtype_next == (lib_ams::FStreamType*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1962        u32 index = ams::StreamType_Hash(0, row.id) & (_db.ind_streamtype_buckets_n - 1);
1963        lib_ams::FStreamType* *prev = &_db.ind_streamtype_buckets_elems[index];
1964        if (retval) {
1965            row.ind_streamtype_next = *prev;
1966            _db.ind_streamtype_n++;
1967            *prev = &row;
1968        }
1969    }
1970    return retval;
1971}
1972
1973// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_streamtype.Remove
1974// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
1975void lib_ams::ind_streamtype_Remove(lib_ams::FStreamType& row) {
1976    if (LIKELY(row.ind_streamtype_next != (lib_ams::FStreamType*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1977        u32 index = ams::StreamType_Hash(0, row.id) & (_db.ind_streamtype_buckets_n - 1);
1978        lib_ams::FStreamType* *prev = &_db.ind_streamtype_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
1979        while (lib_ams::FStreamType *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
1980            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
1981                *prev = next->ind_streamtype_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
1982                _db.ind_streamtype_n--;
1983                row.ind_streamtype_next = (lib_ams::FStreamType*)-1;// not-in-hash
1984                break;
1985            }
1986            prev = &next->ind_streamtype_next;
1987        }
1988    }
1989}
1990
1991// --- lib_ams.FDb.ind_streamtype.Reserve
1992// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
1993void lib_ams::ind_streamtype_Reserve(int n) {
1994    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_streamtype_buckets_n;
1995    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_streamtype_n + n;
1996    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
1997    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
1998        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
1999        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(lib_ams::FStreamType*);
2000        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(lib_ams::FStreamType*);
2001        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
2002        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
2003        lib_ams::FStreamType* *new_buckets = (lib_ams::FStreamType**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
2004        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
2005            FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.out_of_memory  field:lib_ams.FDb.ind_streamtype");
2006        }
2007        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
2008        // rehash all entries
2009        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_streamtype_buckets_n; i++) {
2010            lib_ams::FStreamType* elem = _db.ind_streamtype_buckets_elems[i];
2011            while (elem) {
2012                lib_ams::FStreamType &row        = *elem;
2013                lib_ams::FStreamType* next       = row.ind_streamtype_next;
2014                u32 index          = ams::StreamType_Hash(0, row.id) & (new_nbuckets-1);
2015                row.ind_streamtype_next     = new_buckets[index];
2016                new_buckets[index] = &row;
2017                elem               = next;
2018            }
2019        }
2020        // free old array
2021        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_streamtype_buckets_elems, old_size);
2022        _db.ind_streamtype_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
2023        _db.ind_streamtype_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
2024    }
2025}

2027// --- lib_ams.FDb.zd_ctlin.Insert
2028// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
2029void lib_ams::zd_ctlin_Insert(lib_ams::FStream& row) {
2030    if (!zd_ctlin_InLlistQ(row)) {
2031        lib_ams::FStream* old_tail = _db.zd_ctlin_tail;
2032        row.zd_ctlin_next = NULL;
2033        row.zd_ctlin_prev = old_tail;
2034        _db.zd_ctlin_tail = &row;
2035        lib_ams::FStream **new_row_a = &old_tail->zd_ctlin_next;
2036        lib_ams::FStream **new_row_b = &_db.zd_ctlin_head;
2037        lib_ams::FStream **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
2038        *new_row = &row;
2039        _db.zd_ctlin_n++;
2040    }
2041}

2043// --- lib_ams.FDb.zd_ctlin.Remove
2044// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
2045void lib_ams::zd_ctlin_Remove(lib_ams::FStream& row) {
2046    if (zd_ctlin_InLlistQ(row)) {
2047        lib_ams::FStream* old_head       = _db.zd_ctlin_head;
2048        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
2049        lib_ams::FStream* prev = row.zd_ctlin_prev;
2050        lib_ams::FStream* next = row.zd_ctlin_next;
2051        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
2052        lib_ams::FStream **new_next_a = &prev->zd_ctlin_next;
2053        lib_ams::FStream **new_next_b = &_db.zd_ctlin_head;
2054        lib_ams::FStream **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
2055        *new_next = next;
2056        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
2057        lib_ams::FStream **new_prev_a = &next->zd_ctlin_prev;
2058        lib_ams::FStream **new_prev_b = &_db.zd_ctlin_tail;
2059        lib_ams::FStream **new_prev = next ? new_prev_a : new_prev_b;
2060        *new_prev = prev;
2061        _db.zd_ctlin_n--;
2062        row.zd_ctlin_next=(lib_ams::FStream*)-1; // not-in-list
2063    }
2064}

2070    _db.zd_ctlin_head = NULL;
2071    _db.zd_ctlin_tail = NULL;
2072    _db.zd_ctlin_n = 0;

2075        row->zd_ctlin_next  = (lib_ams::FStream*)-1;
2076        row->zd_ctlin_prev  = NULL;
2077        row = row_next;
2078    }
2079}

2322// --- lib_ams.FFdin.in.BeginRead
2323// Attach fbuf to Iohook for reading
2324// Attach file descriptor and begin reading using edge-triggered epoll.
2325// File descriptor becomes owned by lib_ams::FFdin.in via FIohook field.
2326// Whenever the file descriptor becomes readable, insert fdin into cd_fdin_read.
2327void lib_ams::in_BeginRead(lib_ams::FFdin& fdin, algo::Fildes fd) {
2328    callback_Set1(fdin.in_iohook, fdin, lib_ams::cd_fdin_read_Insert);
2329    fdin.in_iohook.fildes = fd;
2330    IOEvtFlags flags;
2331    read_Set(flags, true);
2332    if (fdin.in_epoll_enable) {
2333        algo_lib::IohookAdd(fdin.in_iohook, flags);
2334    } else {
2335        lib_ams::cd_fdin_read_Insert(fdin);
2336    }
2337}

2348// --- lib_ams.FFdin.in.GetMsg
2349// Detect incoming message in buffer and return it
2350// Look for valid message at current position in the buffer.
2351// If message is already there, return a pointer to it. Do not skip message (call SkipMsg to do that).
2352// If there is no message, read once from underlying file descriptor and try again.
2353// The message is found by looking for delimiter '\n'.
2354// The return value is an aryptr. If ret.elems is non-NULL, the message is valid (possibly empty).
2355// If ret.elems is NULL, no message can be extracted from buffer.
2356// The returned aryptr excludes the trailing deliminter.
2357// SkipMsg will skip both the line and the deliminter.
2358// A partial line at the end of input is NOT returned (TODO?)
2359// 
2360algo::aryptr<char> lib_ams::in_GetMsg(lib_ams::FFdin& fdin) {
2361    algo::aryptr<char> ret;
2362    if (!fdin.in_msgvalid) {
2363        in_Scanmsg(fdin);
2364        if (!fdin.in_msgvalid) {
2365            bool readable = in_Refill(fdin);
2366            if (readable) {
2367                in_Scanmsg(fdin);
2368            }
2369        }
2370    }
2371    char *hdr = (char*)(fdin.in_elems + fdin.in_start);
2372    if (fdin.in_msgvalid) {
2373        ret.elems = hdr;
2374        ret.n_elems = fdin.in_msglen;
2375    }
2376    if (!fdin.in_msgvalid && fdin.in_eof) { // all messages processed
2377        lib_ams::cd_fdin_eof_Insert(fdin);
2378    }
2379    return ret;
2380}
2381
2382// --- lib_ams.FFdin.in.Refill
2383// Refill buffer. Return false if no further refill possible (input buffer exhausted)
2384bool lib_ams::in_Refill(lib_ams::FFdin& fdin) {
2385    bool readable = ValidQ(fdin.in_iohook.fildes);
2386    if (readable) {
2387        int fd     = fdin.in_iohook.fildes.value;
2388        i32 max    = in_Max(fdin);
2389        i32 end    = fdin.in_end;
2390        i32 nbytes = end - fdin.in_start; // # bytes currently in buffer
2391        i32 nfree  = max - end; // bytes available at the end of buffer
2392        if (nbytes == 0 || nfree == 0) { // make more room for reading (or take advantage of free shift)
2393            in_Shift(fdin);
2394            end = fdin.in_end;
2395            nfree = max - end;
2396        }
2397        ssize_t ret         = read(fd, fdin.in_elems + end, nfree);
2398        readable            = !(ret < 0 && errno == EAGAIN);
2399        bool error          = ret < 0 && errno != EAGAIN; // detect permanent error on this fd
2400        bool eof            = error || (ret == 0 && nfree > 0);
2401        fdin.in_end += i32_Max(ret,0); // new end of bytes
2402        if (error) {
2403            fdin.in_err = algo::FromErrno(errno); // fetch errno
2404        }
2405        fdin.in_eof |= eof;
2406    }
2407    if (!readable && fdin.in_epoll_enable) {
2408        lib_ams::cd_fdin_read_Remove(fdin);
2409    }
2410    return readable;
2411}

2413// --- lib_ams.FFdin.in.RemoveAll
2414// Empty bfufer
2415// Discard contents of the buffer.
2416void lib_ams::in_RemoveAll(lib_ams::FFdin& fdin) {
2417    fdin.in_start    = 0;
2418    fdin.in_end      = 0;
2419    fdin.in_msgvalid = false;
2420    fdin.in_msglen   = 0; // reset message length -- important for delimited streams
2421}
2422
2423// --- lib_ams.FFdin.in.Scanmsg
2424// Internal function to scan for a message
2425// 
2426static void lib_ams::in_Scanmsg(lib_ams::FFdin& fdin) {
2427    char *hdr = (char*)(fdin.in_elems + fdin.in_start);
2428    i32 avail = in_N(fdin);
2429    i32 msglen;
2430    bool found = false;
2431    // scan for delimiter starting from the previous place where we left off.
2432    // at the end, save offset back to fdin so we don't have to re-scan.
2433    // returned message length **does not include delimiter**.
2434    // a line that exceeds buffer length is not returned.
2435    for (msglen = fdin.in_msglen; msglen < avail; msglen += sizeof(char)) {
2436        if (hdr[msglen] == '\n') { // delimiter?
2437            found = true;
2438            break;
2439        }
2440    }
2441    if (!found && msglen >= in_Max(fdin)) {
2442        fdin.in_eof = true; // cause user to detect eof
2443        fdin.in_err = algo::FromErrno(E2BIG); // argument list too big -- closest error code
2444    }
2445    fdin.in_msglen = msglen;
2446    fdin.in_msgvalid = found;
2447}
2448
2449// --- lib_ams.FFdin.in.Shift
2450// Internal function to shift data left
2451// Shift existing bytes over to the beginning of the buffer
2452static void lib_ams::in_Shift(lib_ams::FFdin& fdin) {
2453    i32 start = fdin.in_start;
2454    i32 bytes_n = fdin.in_end - start;
2455    if (bytes_n > 0) {
2456        memmove(fdin.in_elems, fdin.in_elems + start, bytes_n);
2457    }
2458    fdin.in_end = bytes_n;
2459    fdin.in_start = 0;
2460}
2461
2462// --- lib_ams.FFdin.in.SkipBytes
2463// Skip N bytes when reading
2464// Mark some buffer contents as read.
2465// 
2466void lib_ams::in_SkipBytes(lib_ams::FFdin& fdin, int n) {
2467    int avail = fdin.in_end - fdin.in_start;
2468    n = i32_Min(n,avail);
2469    fdin.in_start += n;
2470}
2471
2472// --- lib_ams.FFdin.in.SkipMsg
2473// Skip current message, if any
2474// Skip current message, if any.
2475void lib_ams::in_SkipMsg(lib_ams::FFdin& fdin) {
2476    if (fdin.in_msgvalid) {
2477        int skip = fdin.in_msglen;
2478        skip += ssizeof(char); // delimiter
2479        i32 start = fdin.in_start;
2480        start += skip;
2481        fdin.in_start = start;
2482        fdin.in_msgvalid = false;
2483        fdin.in_msglen   = 0; // reset message length -- important for delimited streams
2484    }
2485}
2486
2487// --- lib_ams.FFdin.in.WriteAll
2488// Attempt to write buffer contents to fd
2489// Write bytes to the buffer. If the entire block is written, return true,
2490// Otherwise return false.
2491// Bytes in the buffer are potentially shifted left to make room for the message.
2492// 
2493bool lib_ams::in_WriteAll(lib_ams::FFdin& fdin, u8 *in, i32 in_n) {
2494    int max = in_Max(fdin);
2495    // check if message doesn't fit. if so, shift bytes over.
2496    if (fdin.in_end + in_n > max) {
2497        in_Shift(fdin);
2498    }
2499    // now try to write the message.
2500    i32 end = fdin.in_end;
2501    bool fits = end + in_n <= max;
2502    if (fits && in_n > 0) {
2503        memcpy(fdin.in_elems + end, in, in_n);
2504        fdin.in_end = end + in_n;
2505    }
2506    return fits;
2507}

2545// --- lib_ams.FProc.zd_member_byproc.Cascdel
2546// Delete all elements in the linked list.
2547void lib_ams::zd_member_byproc_Cascdel(lib_ams::FProc& proc) {
2548    while (lib_ams::FMember *zd_member_byproc_first = zd_member_byproc_First(proc)) {
2549        member_Delete(*zd_member_byproc_first);
2550    }
2551}

2553// --- lib_ams.FProc.zd_member_byproc.Insert
2554// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
2555void lib_ams::zd_member_byproc_Insert(lib_ams::FProc& proc, lib_ams::FMember& row) {
2556    if (!zd_member_byproc_InLlistQ(row)) {
2557        lib_ams::FMember* old_tail = proc.zd_member_byproc_tail;
2558        row.zd_member_byproc_next = NULL;
2559        row.zd_member_byproc_prev = old_tail;
2560        proc.zd_member_byproc_tail = &row;
2561        lib_ams::FMember **new_row_a = &old_tail->zd_member_byproc_next;
2562        lib_ams::FMember **new_row_b = &proc.zd_member_byproc_head;
2563        lib_ams::FMember **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
2564        *new_row = &row;
2565        proc.zd_member_byproc_n++;
2566    }
2567}
2568
2569// --- lib_ams.FProc.zd_member_byproc.Remove
2570// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
2571void lib_ams::zd_member_byproc_Remove(lib_ams::FProc& proc, lib_ams::FMember& row) {
2572    if (zd_member_byproc_InLlistQ(row)) {
2573        lib_ams::FMember* old_head       = proc.zd_member_byproc_head;
2574        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
2575        lib_ams::FMember* prev = row.zd_member_byproc_prev;
2576        lib_ams::FMember* next = row.zd_member_byproc_next;
2577        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
2578        lib_ams::FMember **new_next_a = &prev->zd_member_byproc_next;
2579        lib_ams::FMember **new_next_b = &proc.zd_member_byproc_head;
2580        lib_ams::FMember **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
2581        *new_next = next;
2582        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
2583        lib_ams::FMember **new_prev_a = &next->zd_member_byproc_prev;
2584        lib_ams::FMember **new_prev_b = &proc.zd_member_byproc_tail;
2585        lib_ams::FMember **new_prev = next ? new_prev_a : new_prev_b;
2586        *new_prev = prev;
2587        proc.zd_member_byproc_n--;
2588        row.zd_member_byproc_next=(lib_ams::FMember*)-1; // not-in-list
2589    }
2590}

2592// --- lib_ams.FProc.zd_member_byproc.RemoveAll
2593// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
2594void lib_ams::zd_member_byproc_RemoveAll(lib_ams::FProc& proc) {
2595    lib_ams::FMember* row = proc.zd_member_byproc_head;
2596    proc.zd_member_byproc_head = NULL;
2597    proc.zd_member_byproc_tail = NULL;
2598    proc.zd_member_byproc_n = 0;
2599    while (row) {
2600        lib_ams::FMember* row_next = row->zd_member_byproc_next;
2601        row->zd_member_byproc_next  = (lib_ams::FMember*)-1;
2602        row->zd_member_byproc_prev  = NULL;
2603        row = row_next;
2604    }
2605}

2607// --- lib_ams.FProc.zd_member_byproc.RemoveFirst
2608// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
2609lib_ams::FMember* lib_ams::zd_member_byproc_RemoveFirst(lib_ams::FProc& proc) {
2610    lib_ams::FMember *row = NULL;
2611    row = proc.zd_member_byproc_head;
2612    if (row) {
2613        lib_ams::FMember *next = row->zd_member_byproc_next;
2614        proc.zd_member_byproc_head = next;
2615        lib_ams::FMember **new_end_a = &next->zd_member_byproc_prev;
2616        lib_ams::FMember **new_end_b = &proc.zd_member_byproc_tail;
2617        lib_ams::FMember **new_end = next ? new_end_a : new_end_b;
2618        *new_end = NULL;
2619        proc.zd_member_byproc_n--;
2620        row->zd_member_byproc_next = (lib_ams::FMember*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
2621    }
2622    return row;
2623}

2630    zd_proc_Remove(row); // remove proc from index zd_proc

2633// --- lib_ams.FReadfile.buf.Addary
2634// Reserve space (this may move memory). Insert N element at the end.
2635// Return aryptr to newly inserted block.
2636// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), exit program with fatal error.
2637algo::aryptr<u8> lib_ams::buf_Addary(lib_ams::FReadfile& parent, algo::aryptr<u8> rhs) {
2638    bool overlaps = rhs.n_elems>0 && rhs.elems >= parent.buf_elems && rhs.elems < parent.buf_elems + parent.buf_max;
2639    if (UNLIKELY(overlaps)) {
2640        FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.tary_alias  field:lib_ams.FReadfile.buf  comment:'alias error: sub-array is being appended to the whole'");
2641    }
2642    int nnew = rhs.n_elems;
2643    buf_Reserve(parent, nnew); // reserve space
2644    int at = parent.buf_n;
2645    memcpy(parent.buf_elems + at, rhs.elems, nnew * sizeof(u8));
2646    parent.buf_n += nnew;
2647    return algo::aryptr<u8>(parent.buf_elems + at, nnew);
2648}

2650// --- lib_ams.FReadfile.buf.Alloc
2651// Reserve space. Insert element at the end
2652// The new element is initialized to a default value
2653u8& lib_ams::buf_Alloc(lib_ams::FReadfile& parent) {
2654    buf_Reserve(parent, 1);
2655    int n  = parent.buf_n;
2656    int at = n;
2657    u8 *elems = parent.buf_elems;
2658    new (elems + at) u8(0); // construct new element, default initializer
2659    parent.buf_n = n+1;
2660    return elems[at];
2661}

2663// --- lib_ams.FReadfile.buf.AllocAt
2664// Reserve space for new element, reallocating the array if necessary
2665// Insert new element at specified index. Index must be in range or a fatal error occurs.
2666u8& lib_ams::buf_AllocAt(lib_ams::FReadfile& parent, int at) {
2667    buf_Reserve(parent, 1);
2668    int n  = parent.buf_n;
2669    if (UNLIKELY(u64(at) >= u64(n+1))) {
2670        FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.bad_alloc_at  field:lib_ams.FReadfile.buf  comment:'index out of range'");
2671    }
2672    u8 *elems = parent.buf_elems;
2673    memmove(elems + at + 1, elems + at, (n - at) * sizeof(u8));
2674    new (elems + at) u8(0); // construct element, default initializer
2675    parent.buf_n = n+1;
2676    return elems[at];
2677}

2679// --- lib_ams.FReadfile.buf.AllocN
2680// Reserve space. Insert N elements at the end of the array, return pointer to array
2681algo::aryptr<u8> lib_ams::buf_AllocN(lib_ams::FReadfile& parent, int n_elems) {
2682    buf_Reserve(parent, n_elems);
2683    int old_n  = parent.buf_n;
2684    int new_n = old_n + n_elems;
2685    u8 *elems = parent.buf_elems;
2686    memset(elems + old_n, 0, new_n - old_n); // initialize new space
2687    parent.buf_n = new_n;
2688    return algo::aryptr<u8>(elems + old_n, n_elems);
2689}

2691// --- lib_ams.FReadfile.buf.Remove
2692// Remove item by index. If index outside of range, do nothing.
2693void lib_ams::buf_Remove(lib_ams::FReadfile& parent, u32 i) {
2694    u32 lim = parent.buf_n;
2695    u8 *elems = parent.buf_elems;
2696    if (i < lim) {
2697        memmove(elems + i, elems + (i + 1), sizeof(u8) * (lim - (i + 1)));
2698        parent.buf_n = lim - 1;
2699    }
2700}

2703// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
2704void lib_ams::buf_RemoveLast(lib_ams::FReadfile& parent) {

2706    if (n > 0) {

2708        parent.buf_n = n;

2712// --- lib_ams.FReadfile.buf.AbsReserve
2713// Make sure N elements fit in array. Process dies if out of memory
2714void lib_ams::buf_AbsReserve(lib_ams::FReadfile& parent, int n) {
2715    u32 old_max  = parent.buf_max;
2716    if (n > i32(old_max)) {
2717        u32 new_max  = i32_Max(i32_Max(old_max * 2, n), 4);
2718        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(parent.buf_elems, old_max * sizeof(u8), new_max * sizeof(u8));
2719        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
2720            FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.tary_nomem  field:lib_ams.FReadfile.buf  comment:'out of memory'");
2721        }
2722        parent.buf_elems = (u8*)new_mem;
2723        parent.buf_max = new_max;
2724    }
2725}

2854void lib_ams::cbuf_AbsReserve(lib_ams::FReadfile& parent, int n) {
2855    u32 old_max  = parent.cbuf_max;

2861        }
2862        parent.cbuf_elems = (u8*)new_mem;
2863        parent.cbuf_max = new_max;

2913// --- lib_ams.FReadfile.offset.Addary
2914// Reserve space (this may move memory). Insert N element at the end.
2915// Return aryptr to newly inserted block.
2916// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), exit program with fatal error.
2917algo::aryptr<u32> lib_ams::offset_Addary(lib_ams::FReadfile& parent, algo::aryptr<u32> rhs) {
2918    bool overlaps = rhs.n_elems>0 && rhs.elems >= parent.offset_elems && rhs.elems < parent.offset_elems + parent.offset_max;
2919    if (UNLIKELY(overlaps)) {
2920        FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.tary_alias  field:lib_ams.FReadfile.offset  comment:'alias error: sub-array is being appended to the whole'");
2921    }
2922    int nnew = rhs.n_elems;
2923    offset_Reserve(parent, nnew); // reserve space
2924    int at = parent.offset_n;
2925    memcpy(parent.offset_elems + at, rhs.elems, nnew * sizeof(u32));
2926    parent.offset_n += nnew;
2927    return algo::aryptr<u32>(parent.offset_elems + at, nnew);
2928}

2931// Reserve space. Insert element at the end
2932// The new element is initialized to a default value
2933u32& lib_ams::offset_Alloc(lib_ams::FReadfile& parent) {

2935    int n  = parent.offset_n;

2937    u32 *elems = parent.offset_elems;
2938    new (elems + at) u32(0); // construct new element, default initializer
2939    parent.offset_n = n+1;
2940    return elems[at];

2944// Reserve space for new element, reallocating the array if necessary
2945// Insert new element at specified index. Index must be in range or a fatal error occurs.
2946u32& lib_ams::offset_AllocAt(lib_ams::FReadfile& parent, int at) {
2947    offset_Reserve(parent, 1);
2948    int n  = parent.offset_n;

2951    }

2954    new (elems + at) u32(0); // construct element, default initializer
2955    parent.offset_n = n+1;
2956    return elems[at];

3118// --- lib_ams.FStream.zd_member_bystream.Insert
3119// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
3120void lib_ams::zd_member_bystream_Insert(lib_ams::FStream& stream, lib_ams::FMember& row) {
3121    if (!zd_member_bystream_InLlistQ(row)) {
3122        lib_ams::FMember* old_tail = stream.zd_member_bystream_tail;
3123        row.zd_member_bystream_next = NULL;
3124        row.zd_member_bystream_prev = old_tail;
3125        stream.zd_member_bystream_tail = &row;
3126        lib_ams::FMember **new_row_a = &old_tail->zd_member_bystream_next;
3127        lib_ams::FMember **new_row_b = &stream.zd_member_bystream_head;
3128        lib_ams::FMember **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
3129        *new_row = &row;
3130        stream.zd_member_bystream_n++;
3131    }
3132}

3134// --- lib_ams.FStream.zd_member_bystream.Remove
3135// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
3136void lib_ams::zd_member_bystream_Remove(lib_ams::FStream& stream, lib_ams::FMember& row) {
3137    if (zd_member_bystream_InLlistQ(row)) {
3138        lib_ams::FMember* old_head       = stream.zd_member_bystream_head;
3139        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
3140        lib_ams::FMember* prev = row.zd_member_bystream_prev;
3141        lib_ams::FMember* next = row.zd_member_bystream_next;
3142        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
3143        lib_ams::FMember **new_next_a = &prev->zd_member_bystream_next;
3144        lib_ams::FMember **new_next_b = &stream.zd_member_bystream_head;
3145        lib_ams::FMember **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
3146        *new_next = next;
3147        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
3148        lib_ams::FMember **new_prev_a = &next->zd_member_bystream_prev;
3149        lib_ams::FMember **new_prev_b = &stream.zd_member_bystream_tail;
3150        lib_ams::FMember **new_prev = next ? new_prev_a : new_prev_b;
3151        *new_prev = prev;
3152        stream.zd_member_bystream_n--;
3153        row.zd_member_bystream_next=(lib_ams::FMember*)-1; // not-in-list
3154    }
3155}

3283// Insert new element at specified index. Index must be in range or a fatal error occurs.

3330// --- lib_ams.FWritefile.buf.AbsReserve
3331// Make sure N elements fit in array. Process dies if out of memory
3332void lib_ams::buf_AbsReserve(lib_ams::FWritefile& writefile, int n) {
3333    u32 old_max  = writefile.buf_max;
3334    if (n > i32(old_max)) {
3335        u32 new_max  = i32_Max(i32_Max(old_max * 2, n), 4);
3336        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(writefile.buf_elems, old_max * sizeof(u8), new_max * sizeof(u8));
3337        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
3338            FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.tary_nomem  field:lib_ams.FWritefile.buf  comment:'out of memory'");
3339        }
3340        writefile.buf_elems = (u8*)new_mem;
3341        writefile.buf_max = new_max;
3342    }
3343}

3391// --- lib_ams.FWritefile.cbuf.Addary
3392// Reserve space (this may move memory). Insert N element at the end.
3393// Return aryptr to newly inserted block.
3394// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), exit program with fatal error.
3395algo::aryptr<u8> lib_ams::cbuf_Addary(lib_ams::FWritefile& writefile, algo::aryptr<u8> rhs) {
3396    bool overlaps = rhs.n_elems>0 && rhs.elems >= writefile.cbuf_elems && rhs.elems < writefile.cbuf_elems + writefile.cbuf_max;
3397    if (UNLIKELY(overlaps)) {
3398        FatalErrorExit("lib_ams.tary_alias  field:lib_ams.FWritefile.cbuf  comment:'alias error: sub-array is being appended to the whole'");
3399    }
3400    int nnew = rhs.n_elems;
3401    cbuf_Reserve(writefile, nnew); // reserve space
3402    int at = writefile.cbuf_n;
3403    memcpy(writefile.cbuf_elems + at, rhs.elems, nnew * sizeof(u8));
3404    writefile.cbuf_n += nnew;
3405    return algo::aryptr<u8>(writefile.cbuf_elems + at, nnew);
3406}

3542
3543    // lib_ams.FWritefile.buf.Uninit (Tary)  //Message buffer
3544    // remove all elements from lib_ams.FWritefile.buf
3545    buf_RemoveAll(writefile);
3546    // free memory for Tary lib_ams.FWritefile.buf
3547    algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(writefile.buf_elems, sizeof(u8)*writefile.buf_max); // (lib_ams.FWritefile.buf)
3548}

3602// --- lib_ams.FieldId.value.SetStrptrMaybe
3603// Convert string to field.
3604// If the string is invalid, do not modify field and return false.
3605// In case of success, return true
3606bool lib_ams::value_SetStrptrMaybe(lib_ams::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
3607    bool ret = false;
3608    switch (elems_N(rhs)) {
3609        case 5: {
3610            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(rhs[4])<<32)) {
3611                case LE_STR5('v','a','l','u','e'): {
3612                    value_SetEnum(parent,lib_ams_FieldId_value); ret = true; break;
3613                }
3614            }
3615            break;
3616        }
3617    }
3618    return ret;
3619}

3622// Convert string to field.
3623// If the string is invalid, set numeric value to DFLT
3624void lib_ams::value_SetStrptr(lib_ams::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs, lib_ams_FieldIdEnum dflt) {
3625    if (!value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs)) value_SetEnum(parent,dflt);
3626}

3628// --- lib_ams.FieldId.value.ReadStrptrMaybe
3629// Convert string to field. Return success value
3630bool lib_ams::value_ReadStrptrMaybe(lib_ams::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
3631    bool retval = false;
3632    retval = value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs); // try symbol conversion
3633    if (!retval) { // didn't work? try reading as underlying type
3634        retval = i32_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.value,rhs);
3635    }
3636    return retval;
3637}

3669// --- lib_ams.CtlMsg..DispatchRaw
3670int lib_ams::CtlMsgDispatchRaw(lib_ams::CtlMsgCase type, u8 *msg, u32 len) {
3671    int ret = 0;
3672    switch(type) {
3673        case 12: if (sizeof(ams::DumpStreamTableMsg) <= len) {
3674            lib_ams::CtlMsg_DumpStreamTableMsg((ams::DumpStreamTableMsg&)*msg);
3675            ret = (int)sizeof(ams::DumpStreamTableMsg);
3676        } break;
3677        case 4: if (sizeof(ams::ProcAddMsg) <= len) {
3678            lib_ams::CtlMsg_ProcAddMsg((ams::ProcAddMsg&)*msg);
3679            ret = (int)sizeof(ams::ProcAddMsg);
3680        } break;
3681        case 5: if (sizeof(ams::ProcRemoveMsg) <= len) {
3682            lib_ams::CtlMsg_ProcRemoveMsg((ams::ProcRemoveMsg&)*msg);
3683            ret = (int)sizeof(ams::ProcRemoveMsg);
3684        } break;
3685        case 3: if (sizeof(ams::StreamHbMsg) <= len) {
3686            lib_ams::CtlMsg_StreamHbMsg((ams::StreamHbMsg&)*msg);
3687            ret = (int)sizeof(ams::StreamHbMsg);
3688        } break;
3689        default:
3690        break;
3691    }
3692    return ret;
3693}

3697    return CtlMsgDispatchRaw(lib_ams::CtlMsgCase(msg.type), (u8*)&msg, i32(msg.length));
3698}
